YOU'RE RUNNING OUT OF TIME

12:28.218 --> 12:30.921
FOR THIS TO CONTINUE BEING
A CIVIL CONVERSATION.

12:30.921 --> 12:33.153
REALLY, AGENT NOH?

12:33.153 --> 12:37.057
HERE I THOUGHT YOU WERE THE ONE
RUNNING OUT OF TIME.

12:37.057 --> 12:39.159
WHAT'D YOU SAY?

12:39.159 --> 12:42.863
YOU REALLY SHOULD GET OUT THERE
BEFORE IT'S TOO LATE.

12:53.543 --> 12:55.505
I'M NOT--I'M NOT GETTING THIS.

12:55.505 --> 12:58.108
INSTEAD OF FOLLOWING UP
ON THE SOMALIA LEAD,

12:58.108 --> 13:00.510
YOU WANNA REOPEN
THE DIRTY BOMB CASE?
WE NEVER CLOSED IT.

13:00.510 --> 13:03.183
AND SOMALIA IS NOT A LEAD.
IT'S AN URBAN MYTH AT BEST.

13:03.183 --> 13:05.215
MEANWHILE,
BACK ON PLANET EARTH,

13:05.215 --> 13:07.958
WE HAVE A MATERIAL WITNESS--
IN A WEAPONS DEAL.

13:07.958 --> 13:10.991
THAT BROKE ON THE DAY
OF THE BLACKOUT.

13:10.991 --> 13:14.064
OKAY, SO MAYBE IT'S NOT AS SEXY
AS DEAD POULTRY IN AFRICA,

13:14.064 --> 13:17.067
BUT YOU GOTTA ADMIT THE TIMING'S
A LITTLE HINKY HERE, MARK.

13:17.067 --> 13:19.069
IT'S A COINCIDENCE!
SO WHAT IF IT IS?

13:19.069 --> 13:23.103
IT IS A LEGIT LEAD
ON A TERRORISM INVESTIGATION,

13:23.103 --> 13:25.906
WHICH IS KIND OF
WHAT WE DO AROUND HERE.

13:25.906 --> 13:27.807
AGREED.

13:27.807 --> 13:31.912
SEND ME A POSTCARD
FROM INDIO.

13:31.912 --> 13:33.813
YEAH.

13:33.813 --> 13:38.088
WHAT THE HELL'S
THE MATTER WITH YOU?

13:38.088 --> 13:41.091
I JUST WANT TO BE
AN FBI AGENT TODAY. ALL RIGHT?

13:41.091 --> 13:42.953
LIFE IS SHORT.

13:42.953 --> 13:45.956
(woman speaking indistinctly
over P.A.)

13:49.029 --> 13:51.031
(cash register bell dings)

13:56.066 --> 13:59.609
THANK YOU
FOR PUTTING UP WITH ME.

13:59.609 --> 14:01.341
HI, MR. SIMCOE.

14:01.341 --> 14:04.174
I'M AFRAID
I'M THE ANNOYING PARENT

14:04.174 --> 14:06.176
WHO ALWAYS WANTS
A THOUSAND DETAILS.

14:06.176 --> 14:09.519
I'D LIKE TO APOLOGIZE
FOR THAT.

14:11.581 --> 14:14.124
I CAN TELL
IT MAKES YOU UNCOMFORTABLE.

14:14.124 --> 14:17.287
NO, IT DOESN'T. DOESN'T MAKE ME
UNCOMFORTABLE AT ALL.

14:17.287 --> 14:19.429
I'M SORRY ABOUT THE LITTLE
OUTBURST THIS MORNING...

14:19.429 --> 14:21.431
THE TANTRUM IN THE HALLWAY,

14:21.431 --> 14:24.935
THE... UNIDENTIFIED
FLYING MEAL TRAY.

14:26.967 --> 14:28.999
IT'S HIS AUTISM.
MM-HMM.

14:28.999 --> 14:32.002
I-I REALLY DON'T KNOW WHAT TO
SAY TO HIM WHEN HE'S LIKE THAT.

14:32.002 --> 14:34.004
OH, SOMETIMES
YOU CAN'T SAY ANYTHING.

14:34.004 --> 14:36.907
YOU JUST HAVE TO BE THERE.
THANKS.

14:36.907 --> 14:38.048
THANK YOU.

14:38.048 --> 14:39.379
YEAH, UNFORTUNATELY,

14:39.379 --> 14:42.082
I HAVEN'T REALLY BEEN THERE
SINCE OUR SEPARATION.

14:42.082 --> 14:46.516
UH... YOU KNOW,
WORK PICKED UP AND, UM...

14:46.516 --> 14:48.989
WELL, I BARELY KNOW HIM.

14:48.989 --> 14:53.093
WELL, YOU'RE HERE NOW.
IT'S WHAT COUNTS.

14:53.093 --> 14:55.095
A GOOD NIGHT'S SLEEP
MIGHT HELP.

14:55.095 --> 14:58.168
YEAH, WELL, DESPITE THE LUXURY
OF TWO RIGID PLASTIC CHAIRS

14:58.168 --> 15:01.331
IN DYLAN'S ROOM, THE SANDMAN
HAS PROVEN A BIT ELUSIVE.

15:01.331 --> 15:04.334
WELL, YOU SHOULDN'T BE SLEEPING
IN HIS ROOM EVERY NIGHT.
WELL, ACTUALLY,

15:04.334 --> 15:07.437
THE POLICE BROUGHT ME THE KEYS
TO HIS MOTHER'S HOUSE.

15:07.437 --> 15:11.982
I JUST CAN'T BRING MYSELF
TO GO THERE FOR SOME REASON.
WELL, YOU SHOULD TRY.

15:11.982 --> 15:14.284
MAYBE BEING IN DYLAN'S ROOM,
AROUND HIS THINGS...

15:14.284 --> 15:17.147
IT MIGHT GIVE YOU SOME SENSE
OF WHO HE IS.

15:17.147 --> 15:20.991
TOO MUCH TIME IN THE HOSPITAL IS
NOT GOOD FOR ANYONE, MR. SIMCOE.

15:20.991 --> 15:22.993
YOU HANG IN THERE.

15:24.294 --> 15:27.297
HEY, DR. B., I-I GOT THAT SCAN
THAT YOU WANTED.

15:27.297 --> 15:29.299
I WAS JUST GONNA GRAB
A VEGGIE DOG

15:29.299 --> 15:32.462
WHILE IT PRINTS OUT.
TRANSFER DYLAN SIMCOE
TO PHYSICAL THERAPY.

15:32.462 --> 15:37.037
BUT I THOUGHT
YOU WANTED HIM TO--
P.T. CAN HANDLE THE ANTIBIOTICS.
JUST TRANSFER HIM.

15:37.037 --> 15:38.368
OKAY.

15:43.043 --> 15:45.375
â™ªâ™ª

15:45.375 --> 15:49.119
(man) I DON'T UNDERSTAND
WHAT ALL THIS IS ABOUT.
WELCOME TO MY WORLD.

15:49.119 --> 15:52.152
THIS RESTAURANT CAME UP
IN A CONFIDENTIAL INVESTIGATION.

15:52.152 --> 15:54.454
WE NEED THE NAMES AND ADDRESSES
OF EVERY EMPLOYEE.

15:54.454 --> 15:57.157
THE LIST, PLEASE. THANK YOU.

15:57.157 --> 15:58.989
BURGERS AND WAFFLE FRIES--
THAT'S ALL WE DO.

15:58.989 --> 16:00.430
WELL, FOR NOW AT LEAST.

16:00.430 --> 16:03.533
WE'RE GOING TO BE ADDING
FROZEN YOGURT

16:03.533 --> 16:06.296
IN, YOU KNOW, THE FUTURE.
SO THIS PLACE IS OWNED

16:06.296 --> 16:08.298
BY CUSTOMER CHOICE
RESTAURANT GROUP?
UH, THIS PLACE IS

16:08.298 --> 16:10.540
CUSTOMER CHOICE
RESTAURANT GROUP.

16:10.540 --> 16:12.642
UH, WE'RE NOT QUITE
A GROUP YET.

16:12.642 --> 16:16.006
WOULD YOU GIVE ME AND AGENT NOH
A MOMENT, PLEASE?
SURE. YEAH.

16:16.006 --> 16:19.379
UH, SOMEBODY GET SOME BURGERS
FOR THESE FBI GUYS, PLEASE!

16:19.379 --> 16:22.382
WOW, I CAN'T BELIEVE I DIDN'T
WANT TO COME HERE TODAY.

16:22.382 --> 16:24.514
I MEAN, THE INTEL--
THEY'RE ADDING FROZEN YOGURT!

16:24.514 --> 16:26.116
(loud clatter)

16:35.595 --> 16:37.697
FREEZE!

16:39.329 --> 16:40.770
FBI!

16:40.770 --> 16:43.173
AAH! AAH!

16:43.173 --> 16:45.405
(horn honks, tires screech)

16:48.708 --> 16:49.779
(grunts)

16:51.141 --> 16:53.483
AAH!
(grunts)

16:53.483 --> 16:57.687
(trumpet playing in distance)

16:57.687 --> 17:01.451
GO LEFT. GO LEFT.
GOTCHA. GO.

17:01.451 --> 17:05.155
â™ªâ™ª

17:16.136 --> 17:18.037
UHH!
(woman screams)

17:22.112 --> 17:26.116
â™ªâ™ª

17:29.519 --> 17:34.053
(barking and snarling)

17:34.053 --> 17:37.056
(children laughing and shouting
in distance)

17:37.056 --> 17:40.460
(man speaking indistinctly
on TV)

17:45.335 --> 17:47.267
AAH!

17:47.267 --> 17:49.339
UHH!

17:49.339 --> 17:51.541
(both grunt)

17:53.143 --> 17:56.146
(grunting)
COME ON, COME ON,
COME ON!

17:56.146 --> 17:57.447
(Demetri) YOU GOT HIM!

17:57.447 --> 18:01.181
(shouting)
SHUT UP, MAN!

18:01.181 --> 18:03.413
WHAT'S WITH THE JOG, MAN?
(Mark) GET UP.

18:03.413 --> 18:06.456
GET UP!
I THOUGHT WE WERE
JUST COMING IN FOR A BURGER.

18:06.456 --> 18:08.688
(unzips backpack)
ON YOUR KNEES!
GET ON YOUR KNEES!

18:08.688 --> 18:10.690
(Russian accent)
I HEARD WHAT YOU'RE BEING.

18:10.690 --> 18:12.692
FBI CAN BE BITING MY ASS!

18:12.692 --> 18:15.125
OH! HELLO!

18:15.125 --> 18:17.096
YELLOWCAKE URANIUM, MARK.

18:17.096 --> 18:20.099
BLACK MARKET NUCLEAR MATERIAL.
(pants)

18:20.099 --> 18:22.532
OR DO YOU THINK WE SHOULD LEAVE
IT HERE, GO BACK TO YOUR OFFICE

18:22.532 --> 18:25.475
AND STARE
AT YOUR BULLETIN BOARD?
YOU DON'T BE WANTING THIS, YO.

18:25.475 --> 18:27.277
HEY!

18:27.277 --> 18:30.240
YELLOWCAKE.

18:30.240 --> 18:33.883
(case thuds)
IT'S THE TYPE OF STRAIN,
THE TYPE OF WEED HE'S SLINGIN'!

18:33.883 --> 18:36.586
IT'S THE SICKEST STRAIN
'ROUND, YO.

18:36.586 --> 18:39.789
IN MY FLASH-FORWARD,
I'M DRIVING PIMPING RIDE.

18:39.789 --> 18:41.751
19-INCH RIMS, YO.

18:41.751 --> 18:45.325
I MUST BE GOING TO BE
SCARFACE OF POT.

18:45.325 --> 18:47.457
YOU CAN'T
BE FIGHTING FATE, YO.

18:49.529 --> 18:53.633
SHUT UP! SHUT UP!
AAH! AAH! TRUTH HURTS, PIG!

18:53.633 --> 18:56.636
GET OFF OF ME! GET OFF!
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?!

18:56.636 --> 19:00.710
I WAS SICK OF HIS MOUTH!
I'M TALKING ABOUT TODAY!
I'M TALKING ABOUT YOU!

19:00.710 --> 19:02.772
RACIN' AROUND,
LOOKING FOR SOMEONE TO SHOOT!

19:02.772 --> 19:05.175
JUST DROP YOUR PERSONAL CRAP
AND DO YOUR JOB!

19:05.175 --> 19:07.877
HEY, I'M DOING SOMETHING!
I'M NOT SITTING ON MY ASS,

19:07.877 --> 19:11.581
WAITING FOR CLUES TO APPEAR
TO ME IN MY DREAMS!
OH, GIVE IT REST.
THIS ISN'T ABOUT WHAT I SAW.

19:11.581 --> 19:14.224
IT'S ABOUT WHAT YOU DID!
(grunts)

19:17.487 --> 19:19.489
(panting)

19:19.489 --> 19:20.930
MARCH 15th.

19:23.863 --> 19:26.466
THREE SHOTS TO THE CHEST.

19:28.198 --> 19:31.871
I'M NOT JUST GONNA DIE.
I'M GONNA BE MURDERED.

19:40.910 --> 19:44.914
(women speaking indistinctly
on police radio)

19:52.191 --> 19:54.193
HOW'D YOU FIND OUT?

19:56.195 --> 19:58.768
ANONYMOUS CALL.

19:58.768 --> 20:03.633
THE WOMAN SAID SHE READ IT
IN AN INTELLIGENCE BRIEFING.

20:03.633 --> 20:05.635
THAT'S ALL SHE GAVE ME.

20:05.635 --> 20:07.777
(dog barking in distance)

20:07.777 --> 20:09.779
MARK, I'M SORRY
I DIDN'T TELL YOU,

20:09.779 --> 20:13.783
BUT I THOUGHT MAYBE I COULD
FIND WHO'S GONNA KILL ME

20:13.783 --> 20:16.686
OR GET A LEAD ON THEM.
I DON'T KNOW, BUT...

20:16.686 --> 20:20.350
WHY WOULD YOU THINK
THERE'S ANYTHING OUT HERE?

20:20.350 --> 20:23.393
ALDA SAID
I WAS RUNNING OUT OF TIME.

20:23.393 --> 20:25.595
THAT WAS IT?

20:25.595 --> 20:26.756
YEAH.

20:26.756 --> 20:29.959
DEM, ALDA'S A PRO.

20:29.959 --> 20:33.703
SHE KNOWS YOU'RE VULNERABLE,
AND SHE PULLED A NUMBER ON YOU.

20:37.537 --> 20:40.970
(whispers) ALL I CAN HEAR
IS THE CLOCK TICKING.

20:40.970 --> 20:42.842
EVERY DAY.

20:42.842 --> 20:45.345
(normal voice)
WHAT AM I SUPPOSED TO DO?

20:45.345 --> 20:48.548
SOMEHOW...
YOU GET PAST THE FEAR

20:48.548 --> 20:50.019
AND YOU FIGHT.

20:50.019 --> 20:52.882
HOW?
YOU KNOW WHAT I SAW.

20:52.882 --> 20:54.854
(whoosh)

20:54.854 --> 20:58.388
(Mark) I'M IN MY OFFICE,
STARING AT THE MOSAIC BOARD,

20:58.388 --> 20:59.729
AND MEN ARE COMING IN
TO KILL ME.
(whoosh)

20:59.729 --> 21:01.791
YOU AND I ARE PARTNERS.

21:01.791 --> 21:04.263
IF THEY'RE COMING TO KILL ME,
THEY'RE PROBABLY AFTER YOU, TOO,

21:04.263 --> 21:06.496
OR GONNA BE.
IT'S THE FUTURE, MARK.

21:06.496 --> 21:09.439
W-WHY DO YOU THINK
YOU CAN STOP IT?
BECAUSE WE SAW IT.

21:09.439 --> 21:13.002
WE CAN USE WHAT WE SAW
TO STOP WHAT WE SAW.

21:13.002 --> 21:16.976
DEMETRI, WE CAN SOLVE
YOUR MURDER BEFORE IT HAPPENS.

21:16.976 --> 21:20.880
THAT'S WHY I WANNA PUT
EVERYTHING WE HAVE ON MOSAIC.

21:20.880 --> 21:24.283
FOR YOU. FOR ME.
FOR EVERYBODY.

21:32.662 --> 21:33.923
(bird calling)

21:33.923 --> 21:36.626
NOW CAN WE GET OUT OF HERE?

21:38.668 --> 21:41.000
YEAH. WE CAN.

21:41.000 --> 21:43.703
OH, EXCUSE ME.

21:43.703 --> 21:44.934
HEY, MR. SIMCOE.

21:44.934 --> 21:47.377
STEPPING OUT FOR A BIT?

21:47.377 --> 21:50.309
JUST, UH,
FOLLOWING SOME ADVICE.
OH.

21:50.309 --> 21:52.812
I THINK YOU LEFT THIS
IN DYLAN'S ROOM.

21:52.812 --> 21:55.985
OH, UH... THANKS.

21:55.985 --> 21:57.647
SHE'S BEAUTIFUL.
YEAH.

21:57.647 --> 21:59.318
YOUR GIRLFRIEND?

21:59.318 --> 22:01.851
UM, WE HAVEN'T ACTUALLY MET.

22:01.851 --> 22:03.593
COMING UP SOON,

22:03.593 --> 22:06.856
A GLENDALE POSTAL WORKER
USES THE MOSAIC WEB SITE

22:06.856 --> 22:08.858
TO MEET THE POLICE OFFICER
HE BELIEVES

22:08.858 --> 22:10.860
IS GOING TO SAVE HIS LIFE
IN THE COMING MONTHS.

22:10.860 --> 22:13.833
YOU WON'T WANNA MISS THIS.
BUT FIRST...

22:13.833 --> 22:16.536
AH, IT'S INCREDIBLE,
ISN'T IT?

22:16.536 --> 22:18.908
A TEMPORAL ANOMALY
IN GLOBAL CONSCIOUSNESS.

22:18.908 --> 22:21.411
YEAH, I THINK THAT QUALIFIES.

22:21.411 --> 22:23.373
SO WHAT'D YOU SEE?

22:24.944 --> 22:27.947
OH, I GUESS THIS IS THE NEW
"HOW'S THE WEATHER," ISN'T IT?

22:33.022 --> 22:35.054
WELL, THEN...

22:35.054 --> 22:36.886
WHY NOT? UM...

22:36.886 --> 22:38.728
(whoosh)
(Lloyd) I WAS IN A HOUSE--

22:38.728 --> 22:41.561
UH, NOT MY OWN HOUSE.
I GOT A CALL FROM SOMEONE.

22:41.561 --> 22:43.963
I DON'T KNOW WHO IT WAS,
BUT IT WAS URGENT.

22:43.963 --> 22:47.967
DYLAN WAS NEARBY,
MAYBE IN ANOTHER ROOM.

22:47.967 --> 22:51.000
I HEARD A WOMAN'S VOICE...
(Olivia) HEY, HONEY.

22:51.000 --> 22:52.972
I TURNED TOWARDS IT...

22:52.972 --> 22:55.044
AND IT WAS OVER.

22:55.044 --> 22:57.707
UM, I NEVER SAW HER FACE.

22:57.707 --> 23:00.810
BUT I KNEW
THAT WE WERE TOGETHER...

23:02.051 --> 23:04.754
THAT SHE WAS
IMPORTANT TO ME SOMEHOW.

23:04.754 --> 23:07.417
I KNOW EXACTLY WHAT YOU MEAN.

23:07.417 --> 23:09.919
HERE'S THE SCAN, DOCTOR.
THANK YOU.

23:09.919 --> 23:12.962
UM, EXCUSE ME ONE--
ONE SECOND. I'M SORRY.

23:12.962 --> 23:14.864
DR. BENFORD!

23:14.864 --> 23:17.066
DR. B. DR. B.!

23:17.066 --> 23:18.768
NED'S C.T.

23:18.768 --> 23:20.430
OH, GREAT.

23:21.971 --> 23:24.003
WHOA. BIG HEMATOMA.

23:24.003 --> 23:26.576
BLOOD'S BEEN GATHERING AROUND
THE LIVER SINCE THE BUS CRASH.

23:26.576 --> 23:28.778
NED'S LUCKY HE SHOWED UP HERE
IN TIME.

23:28.778 --> 23:30.910
WELL, N-NO, IT'S NOT LUCK.

23:30.910 --> 23:33.042
IT'S... I MEAN,
HE WAS ALIVE IN HIS VISION.

23:33.042 --> 23:35.044
SO CLEARLY HE MADE IT
TO THE HOSPITAL--

23:35.044 --> 23:37.046
OH, GOD. ENOUGH ABOUT
THE VISIONS, DR. VARLEY.

23:37.046 --> 23:40.049
NO, DR. BENFORD,
IT'S RELEVANT DATA.
IT'S NOT DATA.

23:40.049 --> 23:43.553
IT'S NOT DATA ANY MORE THAN
THE DREAM I HAD LAST NIGHT.

23:43.553 --> 23:46.756
LOOK, I-I DON'T UNDERSTAND
HOW YOU CAN IGNORE SOMETHING

23:46.756 --> 23:49.459
THAT EVEN THE MOST SKEPTICAL
PEOPLE IN THE WORLD

23:49.459 --> 23:51.461
THINK MIGHT BE REAL.

23:51.461 --> 23:53.463
I'M NOT IGNORING
THE FLASH-FORWARDS.

23:53.463 --> 23:56.466
I'M JUST NOT BRINGING THEM
INTO THE PRACTICE OF MEDICINE.

23:56.466 --> 23:59.469
NOW CONSENT MR. NED FOR SURGERY
AND MEET ME IN THE O.R.

24:02.542 --> 24:05.044
OH, WITH ANY SURGERY,
THERE'S A RISK OF INFECTION,

24:05.044 --> 24:09.018
BLOOD LOSS, DRUG ALLERGY
AND EVEN DEATH, NED.

24:09.018 --> 24:10.980
IT'S AL GRAVY.

24:10.980 --> 24:14.053
(clicks pen)
YOU KNOW, IT'S OKAY
IF YOU'VE GOT QUESTIONS

24:14.053 --> 24:15.725
OR IF YOU'RE WORRIED.

24:15.725 --> 24:18.027
UH, THIS IS A MAJOR SURGERY.
I GET IT.

24:18.027 --> 24:20.029
YOU'RE TELLING ME I NEED

24:20.029 --> 24:22.492
SOME SORT
OF DRUG ALLERGY-DEATH SURGERY.

24:22.492 --> 24:24.534
I'M TOTALLY COOL WITH IT.

24:24.534 --> 24:26.536
I MEAN, I KNOW
IT SOUNDS WEIRD, BUT..

24:26.536 --> 24:28.568
SOME KIND OF CHANGE
IS HAPPENING.

24:28.568 --> 24:33.072
I MEAN, I DON'T FEEL NERVOUS
OR AFRAID OF, LIKE, ANYTHING.

24:33.072 --> 24:35.775
I MEAN, ALL THAT WORRYING
ALL THE TIME,

24:35.775 --> 24:37.246
IT'S JUST, LIKE,

24:37.246 --> 24:40.880
KEPT ME FROM BEING
THE ME I'M SUPPOSED TO BE.

24:40.880 --> 24:43.482
SIX MONTHS FROM NOW,
I SEE MYSELF,

24:43.482 --> 24:47.086
AND I'M, LIKE, THIS INVINCIBLE,
FEARLESS BLACK GUY,

24:47.086 --> 24:49.158
LIKE SHAFT OR BRYANT GUMBEL.

24:49.158 --> 24:52.692
AND KNOWING THAT...

24:52.692 --> 24:54.223
IT'S ALREADY CHANGED ME.

25:00.800 --> 25:03.072
(children laughing
and shouting indistinctly)

25:03.072 --> 25:06.576
(bell tolling)

25:06.576 --> 25:08.938
(door opens)
(man speaks indistinctly)

25:08.938 --> 25:10.109
OH.

25:10.109 --> 25:13.643
YES. YES, RABBI HIRSCHOLTZ.

25:13.643 --> 25:16.085
OH,
15 IN THE LAST 2 WEEKS.

25:16.085 --> 25:18.588
FOUR, UH, ON SUNDAY,
ACTUALLY.

25:18.588 --> 25:22.051
I DIDN'T LEAVE THE CEMETERY
UNTIL AFTER SUNDOWN. BYE.

25:22.051 --> 25:25.024
OH, I'M SORRY.
I'M SO SORRY ABOUT EVERYTHING.

25:25.024 --> 25:27.627
I'VE BEEN SO BUSY
WITH EVERYTHING.

25:27.627 --> 25:29.899
SO HOW CAN I HELP YOU?

25:29.899 --> 25:31.200
I, UM...

25:31.200 --> 25:33.963
(crickets chirping)

25:33.963 --> 25:35.965
OH, I'M SOR-- (laughs)

25:35.965 --> 25:37.907
I KEEP CRICKETS.

25:37.907 --> 25:41.571
OH, I REALLY--I REALLY
LIKE THE WAY THEY SOUND.

25:41.571 --> 25:44.814
SO, PAIGE, YOU WERE SAYING?

25:44.814 --> 25:47.977
PAIGE IS MY SISTER.
I'M NICOLE.

25:47.977 --> 25:50.680
OH.
I ONLY COME ON CHRISTMAS

25:50.680 --> 25:51.981
AND SOMETIMES ON EASTER.

25:51.981 --> 25:53.983
BUT THAT'S GONNA CHANGE.

25:53.983 --> 25:56.055
I, UM, I WANNA HELP OUT.

25:56.055 --> 25:58.157
I WANNA START DOING
SOME VOLUNTEER WORK,

25:58.157 --> 26:00.229
IN THE MORNING
BEFORE I HAVE WORK AND--

26:00.229 --> 26:02.932
THAT'S GREAT. UH, BUT AS FAR
AS VOLUNTEER WORK GOES,

26:02.932 --> 26:04.293
WE ARE FULL UP.

26:04.293 --> 26:08.998
SEE, IN A CRISIS LIKE THIS,
PEOPLE--THEY REALLY WANNA...

26:08.998 --> 26:10.870
WELL, PEOPLE NEED TO HELP.

26:10.870 --> 26:15.975
UH, WHY DON'T YOU--WHY DON'T YOU
TELL ME WHAT THIS IS ALL ABOUT?

26:15.975 --> 26:17.977
(whoosh)

26:20.780 --> 26:24.083
HOW DO I ATONE FOR SOMETHING
I HAVEN'T DONE YET?

26:27.116 --> 26:28.317
UH...

26:28.317 --> 26:31.891
IN MY FLASH-FORWARD,
I FELT LIKE I WAS BEING...

26:31.891 --> 26:33.062
PUNISHED.

26:33.062 --> 26:34.223
(whoosh)

26:34.223 --> 26:36.696
DO YOU THINK...

26:36.696 --> 26:38.698
DO YOU THINK
GOD MADE THIS HAPPEN?

26:41.600 --> 26:44.103
Y-Y-YOU KNOW, IT'S--
IT'S REALLY HARD TO BELIEVE

26:44.103 --> 26:48.037
THAT THERE'S NOT A DIVINE HAND
INVOLVED SOMEHOW.

26:48.037 --> 26:50.840
TELL YOU WHAT.

26:50.840 --> 26:56.045
THIS RIGHT HERE IS
AUDREY RIDGEWAY'S PHONE NUMBER.

26:56.045 --> 26:58.347
SHE IS
THE VOLUNTEER COORDINATOR.

26:58.347 --> 27:00.089
(rips paper)

27:00.089 --> 27:03.222
I HOPE SHE CAN HELP.
(sets down pen)

27:03.222 --> 27:05.725
HERE'S A T-SHIRT.
(clears throat)

27:05.725 --> 27:07.697
BYE.

27:07.697 --> 27:09.398
(door opens)

27:09.398 --> 27:12.231
(door closes)

27:12.231 --> 27:14.233
(typing)

27:31.751 --> 27:33.753
WHERE'S NED?
O.R. TOOK HIM.

27:33.753 --> 27:36.055
WHEN?
10, 15 MINUTES AGO.
WHAT'S WRONG?

27:36.055 --> 27:39.829
CALL THE O.R.
WE'RE ABOUT TO KILL OUR PATIENT.

27:46.736 --> 27:50.299
(monitor beeping steadily)

27:50.299 --> 27:52.101
DR. BENFORD,

27:52.101 --> 27:54.373
WE CAN'T OPERATE.

27:54.373 --> 27:57.376
I COULDN'T FIGURE IT OUT.
I COULDN'T MAKE SENSE OF IT.

27:57.376 --> 28:01.080
BUT NOW I'VE GOT IT.
NED HAS ADDISON'S DISEASE.

28:01.080 --> 28:02.752
SURGERY COULD KILL HIM.

28:02.752 --> 28:04.884
IN THE BUS CRASH,
HE WAS CALM

28:04.884 --> 28:07.356
IN THE FACE
OF AN INSANE DISASTER.

28:07.356 --> 28:09.859
AND AGAIN TODAY, HE SPOKE
ABOUT HIS FLASH-FORWARD.

28:09.859 --> 28:14.023
OH, BRYCE, PLEASE.
AND AGAIN HE MENTIONED THAT
HE WAS WEIRDLY CALM AND BLACK.

28:14.023 --> 28:17.166
YOU BETTER SCRUB
IF YOU WANT IN ON THIS CASE.
IF HE'S GOT ADDISON'S,

28:17.166 --> 28:20.329
THEN HIS BODY IS MAKING MELANIN
COMPOUNDS INSTEAD OF ADRENALINE.

28:20.329 --> 28:23.302
THAT'S WHY HIS SKIN
IS GOING TO GET DARK.
YEAH. I KNOW WHAT
ADDISON'S DISEASE IS.

28:23.302 --> 28:25.805
AND WITHOUT ADRENALINE,

28:25.805 --> 28:27.807
HIS BODY CAN'T MOUNT
A PROPER STRESS RESPONSE.

28:27.807 --> 28:30.339
THAT'S WHY HE'S SO SERENE
IN THE FACE OF THIS SURGERY.
UGH! BRYCE! STOP!

28:30.339 --> 28:31.981
AND WITHOUT
THE STRESS HORMONES,

28:31.981 --> 28:35.084
HIS BODY WILL BE UNABLE
TO ADAPT TO SURGERY.

28:35.084 --> 28:38.387
NO, WITHOUT SURGERY HE'LL DIE.
HIS BLOOD PRESSURE WILL TANK
AND HE'LL DIE. LISTEN...

28:38.387 --> 28:40.920
YOU'RE NOT LISTENING TO ME.
IN HIS VISION, HE SAW--

28:40.920 --> 28:42.221
ENOUGH ABOUT VISIONS!

28:42.221 --> 28:43.923
HE NEEDS HYDROCORTISONE.

28:43.923 --> 28:45.925
NO, I'M NOT ADMINISTERING
A POTENTIALLY HARMFUL DRUG

28:45.925 --> 28:48.928
BECAUSE A PATIENT HAD
A FREAKY DREAM.
THESE AREN'T DREAMS.

28:48.928 --> 28:51.230
LOOK, I DON'T KNOW WHAT YOU SAW,
AND I DON'T CARE.

28:51.230 --> 28:53.402
BUT IT IS AFFECTING
YOUR PROFESSIONAL JUDGMENT,

28:53.402 --> 28:57.066
AND IT NEEDS TO STOP.
HOW ABOUT
YOUR PROFESSIONAL JUDGMENT?

28:57.066 --> 29:00.039
EXCUSE ME?
COME ON, DR. BENFORD. YOU KNOW
WHY YOU DON'T WANT TO BELIEVE...

29:00.039 --> 29:03.112
OH, YOU DON'T WANT
TO DO THIS, BRYCE.
IN YOUR FLASH-FORWARD.

29:03.112 --> 29:06.445
YOU SAID IT YOURSELF. YOU SAW
THE END OF YOUR MARRIAGE.
OH, YOU ARE SO OUT OF LINE,
DOCTOR.

29:06.445 --> 29:08.747
AND YOU STICKING YOUR HEAD
IN THE SAND

29:08.747 --> 29:11.450
IS GONNA END UP KILLING
OUR PATIENT.
NO. YOU KNOW WHAT'S GONNA
KILL OUR PATIENT?

29:11.450 --> 29:13.282
WASTING ANY MORE TIME ARGUING

29:13.282 --> 29:15.785
BECAUSE HE'S LYING ON THAT TABLE
CONTINUING TO BLEED.

29:15.785 --> 29:18.087
NOW THAT'S NOT FROM
A MAGIC 8 BALL OR A OUIJA BOARD

29:18.087 --> 29:20.089
OR SOME KIND OF VISION.

29:20.089 --> 29:23.762
RIGHT HERE, RIGHT NOW,
THAT'S REAL.

29:23.762 --> 29:26.065
YOU KNOW WHAT?
DON'T BOTHER SCRUBBING IN.

29:26.065 --> 29:29.468
(monitor continues beeping
steadily)

